<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911022-0048</DOCNO><DOCID>911022-0048.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Crane Co.:   Manufacturer Reports Drop   Of 24% in 3rd-Quarter Net</HL><DATE>10/22/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A13B</SO><CO>   CR</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Crane Co., hurting from a weak economy, reported a 24%drop in third-quarter net income and warned that recessionaryconditions would continue to hurt it in the fourth quarter.   The New York manufacturer of engineered industrialproducts posted net of $13 million, or 41 cents a share, downfrom $17.1 million, or 53 cents a share, a year earlier.Sales were $342 million, down 8% from $372 million.</LP><TEXT>   Crane said its business was hurt by the weak economy inthe U.S., Canada and Britain and by lower production levelsas the company continued to reduce inventories.</TEXT></DOC>